ENTRY            41784   20250905   20260518   20260518       4228
SUBENT        41784001   20250905   20260518   20260518       4228
BIB                 15         56
TITLE      Studies of angular distributions and cross sections
           of gamma-ray radiation on Si and O nuclei in reactions
           with fast neutrons
AUTHOR     (A.V.Andreev,N.A.Fedorov,D.N.Grozdanov,P.S.Prusachenko,
           Yu.N.Kopach, T.Yu.Tretyakova, G.V.Pampushik, C.Hramco,
           A.P.Zuev, P.G.Filonchik, P.I.Kharlamov, I.N.Ruskov,
           V.R.Skoy)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB)
           (4RUSMOS)
           (3BULBLA)
           (4RUSMFT) Moscow Institute of Physics and Technology
            (National Research University), Moscow, 117303 Russia
REFERENCE  (J,BAS,89,1254,2025)
           #doi:10.1134/S1062873825712012
           Engl.translation of:
           (J,IZV,89,1241,2025)  Issue 8
FACILITY   (NGEN,4ZZZDUB) Portable ING-27 neutron generator
INC-SOURCE (D-T)
SAMPLE      Chemically pure natural SiO(2) powder of 1.6 g/cm3
           density in 3-mm-thick polyethylene container of
           200 x 200 x 200 mm internal dimensions.
            Si-28 - 92.230 %, Si-29 - 4.683 %, Si-30 - 3.087 %.
            O-16 - 99.762 %, O-17 - 0.0380 %, O-18 - 0.2000 %.
METHOD     (COINC)
           (ASSOP)
           (TOF)
DETECTOR   (PS) Built in ING-27 position-sensitive alpha-particle
           detector to estimate direction of neutron ( from
           d(t,alpha)n reaction) movement.
           (HPGE) Two ORTEC GMX60P4-83 located at a horizontal
           plane at angles of +-60 deg.
           (SCIN) Four LaBr(3)(Ce) scintillators placed at
           vertical plane at angles 25, 40, 60, 70 deg.
ANALYSIS    Angular dif. cross-sections of gamma emission were
           determined by formula (1) in BAS,89,1254,2025.
CORRECTION  Background was measured by empty sample.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) Average estimated error in the overall
           gamma-ray detection efficiency for both HPGe and
           LaBr3(Ce) detectors, including errors in the setup
           geometry - 11%.
           (ERR-2) Average error in determining the coverage
           factor of the target by the neutron beam  - 11%.
           (ERR-3,,2.) Errors associated with the number of
            nuclei in the sample < 2%.
           (ERR-4,,15.) Correction for multiple scattering
           (ERR-S) Statistical error
COMMENT     Of authors.
           .This work was supported by the Russian Science
            Foundation (project no. 23-12-00239).
           .Request of angular distribution data was sent
            16.09.2025 to A.V.Andreev,N.A.Fedorov,Yu.N.Kopach.
            Reply of A.Andreev - data are preliminary and
            angular distributions are not ready for EXFOR.
STATUS     (PRELM) Preliminary data (comment of the author
            A.Andreev).
HISTORY    (20250905C) M.M.
ENDBIB              56
COMMON               3          3
EN         ERR-1      ERR-2
MEV        PER-CENT   PER-CENT
 14.1       11.        11.
ENDCOMMON            3
