BIB                  5         28
REACTION   (14-SI-0(N,X)14-SI-28,PAR,SIG,G)
            Si28(n,inl)Si28 and Si29(n,2n)Si28 contribution.
ANALYSIS    Cross-section SIG was determined from measured angular
            distributions dSIG/dOmega fitted by sum of
            Legendre polynomials in a form
             dSIG/dOmega =(SIG/4PI)*(1 + Sum( a(L)P(L)))
           .Energies of gamma-quanta, spins, parities, energies of
            the initial and final states were taken from NuDat3.
            Egamma,keV   Jp-ini    Jp-fin   TALYS-1.97 calculation
            1779.0        2+        0+       354. mb
COMMENT    Of compiler.
           Formula (1) was applied for determination of angular
           distribution, where n in the denominator of formula (1)
           is explained as "the abundance of the isotope on which
           the reaction occurred". For contribution of two
           reactions Si28(n,inl)Si28 and Si29(n,2n)Si28 in this
           Subent it's not clear what value of n was used -
           the abundance of Si28 or sum of abundances Si28 + Si29.
REL-REF    (D,,S.P.Simakov+,R,INDC(CCP)-413,1998)
            403+-18 mb
           (D,20493008,U.Abbondanno+,J,JNE,27,227,1973)
            374+-9 mb
           (D,20866003,K.Connell+,J,ARI,26,71,1975)
            426+-9 mb
           (D,32688028,H.-Y.Zhou+,J,NIM/A,648,(1),192,2011)
            373+-15 mb
STATUS     (TABLE,,A.V.Andreev+,J,BAS,89,1254,2025) Table 2
           (DEP,41784011) Legendre coefficients.
